<TITLE> SSC exams delayed for SA Games </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Jan 11 (bdnews24.com) The start of the Secondary School Certificate exams will be pushed back to from Feb 1 to Feb 11, due to the 11th South Asian Games, an official said Monday. Education ministry spokesperson Shubodh Chandra Dhali told bdnews24.com the exams were being delayed to make way for the 10-day Games, to be launched on January 29, which will see nearly 2,000 participants descend on Dhaka. The ministry of youth and sports asked for rescheduling of the exams, mainly to prevent huge traffic congestion in the capital. An inter-ministerial meeting last week also decided to keep shops and businesses around the games venues shut during the event for security measures, public relation officer of the ministry Shafiqur Rahman told bdnews24.com. The games will be held at 23 venues around the country under management of the Bangladesh Olympic Association (BOA). Some 1,800 players and officials will join the event, which ministers and senior delegates from participating countries will also attend
